What best illustrates active listening on the part of a second-grade teacher who is helping a student solve a personal problem? The best illustration of active listening on the part of a second-grade teacher who is helping a student solve a personal problem is when the teacher repeats back to the student what the student has said, to ensure that the teacher has heard and understood the student correctly. The teacher may also ask questions to clarify any points that are not clear, and make sure that the student feels heard and understood.

electron, dipole, force, mass. the differences in deuterium chloride (DCl) and hydrogen chloride (HCl) is due to The difference in deuterium chloride (DCl) and hydrogen chloride (HCl) is due to the difference in mass. Deuterium has a mass that is twice that of hydrogen, so the deuterium chloride molecule is heavier. This difference in mass results in a difference in the forces between the molecules, which leads to different properties for the two substances.
